<div>
80% of software engineers will <a href="https://www.itpro.com/software/software-engineers-are-in-for-a-rough-ride-as-ai-adoption-ramps-up-80-percent-will-be-forced-to-upskill-by-2027-as-the-profession-is-transformed">need to upskill by 2027</a> to keep pace with generative AI's growing demands, according to Gartner. The consultancy predicts AI will transform the industry in three phases. Initially, AI tools will boost productivity, particularly for senior developers. Subsequently, "AI-native software engineering" will emerge, with most code generated by AI. Long-term, AI engineering will rise as enterprise adoption increases, requiring a new breed of professionals skilled in software engineering, data science, and machine learning.<br>
